@arg repository-transition/invariants
@title Role × Value Invariants
@sigils [👓/支 🌱/门]
@instantiated-by ["Different deposit workflows, object types, permissions," "and metadata needs across Depositors, Archivists, Students."]
@instantiated-by ["Requirements for audit trails, rights metadata," "ethical checks, embargo governance."]
@instantiated-by ["Need for metadata openness, interdisciplinary connections," "APIs, stable identifiers, reuse signals."]
@instantiated-by ["Workflows that minimise administrative load and allow" "easy, fair contribution."]

! conclusion: Role × Value invariants that must be preserved in transformation

  + THEN: Operate an explicit move on the named axis (see substructure below); steward the pattern against the declared discipline.
    + lemma: Infrastructure must support plural forms of visibility and contribution.

    + lemma: The repository must make research trustworthy by design.

    + lemma: Infrastructure must support flexible, linkable, cross-disciplinary reuse.

    + lemma: The repository must reduce friction and support sharing without penalty.

  + because: We ARE diverse stakeholders interacting with the research ecosystem,
             and we BELIEVE in Inclusivity,

  + because: We ARE accountable actors (Governance, Assessors, Archivists, Students),
             and we BELIEVE in Confidence and Responsibility,

  + because: We ARE creators (Depositors) and reusers (Downloaders),
             and we BELIEVE in Enterprising Creativity and Connectedness,

  + because: We ARE a community producing and sharing research,
             and we BELIEVE in Generosity of Spirit,
